descp2: int, optional (default=2) The average number of labels per instance. More precisely, the number of labels per sample is drawn from a Poisson distribution with ``n_labels`` as its expected value, but samples are bounded (using rejection sampling) by ``n_classes``, and must be nonzero if ``allow_unlabeled`` is False.
